S108.shortDescription: Nested blocks of code should not be left empty
S108.fullDescription: Most of the time a block of code is empty when a piece of code is really missing. So such empty block must be either filled or removed.

S1168.shortDescription: Empty arrays and collections should be returned instead of null
S1168.fullDescription: Returning null instead of an actual array, collection or map forces callers of the method to explicitly test for nullity, making them more complex and less readable.

S1172.shortDescription: Unused method parameters should be removed
S1172.fullDescription: Unused parameters are misleading. Whatever the values passed to such parameters, the behavior will be the same.

S125.shortDescription: Sections of code should not be commented out
S125.fullDescription: Programmers should not comment out code as it bloats programs and reduces readability.

S1481.shortDescription: Unused local variables should be removed
S1481.fullDescription: If a local variable is declared but not used, it is dead code and should be removed. Doing so will improve maintainability because developers will not wonder what the variable is used for.

S2486.shortDescription: Generic exceptions should not be ignored
S2486.fullDescription: When exceptions occur, it is usually a bad idea to simply ignore them. Instead, it is better to handle them properly, or at least to log them.

S3241.shortDescription: Methods should not return values that are never used
S3241.fullDescription: Private methods are clearly intended for use only within their own scope. When such methods return values that are never used by any of their callers, then clearly there is no need to actually make the return, and it should be removed in the interests of efficiency and clarity.

S3265.shortDescription: Non-flags enums should not be used in bitwise operations
S3265.fullDescription: enums are usually used to identify distinct elements in a set of values. However enums can be treated as bit fields and bitwise operations can be used on them to combine the values. This is a good way of specifying multiple elements of set with a single value. When enums are used this way, it is a best practice to mark the enum with the FlagsAttribute.

S3776.shortDescription: Cognitive Complexity of methods should not be too high
S3776.fullDescription: Cognitive Complexity is a measure of how hard the control flow of a method is to understand. Methods with high Cognitive Complexity will be difficult to maintain.

S4487.fullDescription: Private fields only used to store values without reading them later is a case of dead store. So changing the value of such field is useless and most probably indicates a serious error in the code.
